        <h1>Welcome ! </h1>
        <p>This repository provides technical information on the upcoming
          version 2.0 of the standard.</p>
        <p>SData is to be understood as a web toolkit promoting the development
          of REST-orientated services and their consumption. Centered around a
          small, standards-based core (HTTP, ATOM, JSON), SData provides a
          choice of mechanisms solving common challenges in a consistent manner.<br>
        </p>
        <p>SData is successfully used to deliver a number of key projects and is
          recognized as an important building block in the Sage technology
          strategy. The version 2.0 of the standard focuses its attention on
          needs beyond the traditional application integration - it delivers
          additions aimed towards the needs of web product- and interface
          definitions. <br>
        </p>
        <p><br>
        </p>
        <p>The focal points of the new release are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Specification of the JSON format for SData information exchanges</li>
          <li>Decrease the number of restrictive aspects imposed by SData
            resulting in a smaller and better defined specification core</li>
          <li>Maintain compatibility with the SData 1.1 version, ensuring that
            SData 1.1 implementations are automatically version 2.0 compliant</li>
          <li>Clarify the role and form of contracts</li>
          <li> Reorganization of the standard, stressing the freedom of choice
            for development teams and architects</li>
        </ul>
        <ul>
        </ul>
        &nbsp;
        <p></p>
        The documents contained in our GitHub file repository preview a number
        of important aspects of the standard's upcoming release. They are to be
        considered working drafts. We will continue to update and extend the
        information as we make progress towards the release. <br>
        <p></p>
        <p>We welcome your visit of <a href="https://github.com/tudor06/TudorTestRepository/tree/master/doc">our
            file repository.</a><br>
          <br>
        </p>
        <p>You may also find these SData related projects of interest:<br>
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Sage/argos-sdk">Argos-SDK</a>:
            framework for creating SData-powered mobile applications using
            HTML5, CSS and Javascript</li>
          <li><a href="http://argos-template">Argos-template</a>: template
            project for Argos</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Sage/SDataJavaScriptClientLib">SDataJavaScriptClientLib</a>:
            JavaScript library aiding the consumption of SData services</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Sage/SDataCSharpClientLib">SDataCSharpClientLib</a>:
            C# library aiding the consumption of SData services</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Sage/SData-Contracts">SData contracts</a>:
            a library of schema-based contracts supported by some Sage
            applications</li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/Sage/acts_as_sdata">Acts-as-SData</a>:
            a Ruby implementation of the SData protocol</li>
        </ul>
